<br>
Effect? You guessed it. Sends target to zone &quot;safe point&quot;. No confirmation box, because it's considered an Evac, and it's in-zone only. Thus, no problems like TL's had, when people were being an ass sending people all over Norrath (thus the Box) without asking. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utalamanthalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talamanthalon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/25/02 8:45:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Decession</span><hr size=1> Gremer-<br>
<br>
It speeds it up because.<br>
<br>
a) You don't have to zone with group absond every single phreaking time your moving a group across SG.<br>
<br>
b) You can now bind at TOV entrance, and just stay at the sg/cs zone line and trans pple.  When your done, bam you gate and your at TOV for the raid.<br>
<br>
c) With bind point kept at TOV you can now port out to CS swim to sg and trans, then gate back.  Missing VERY little raid time.  Even better if you are the only absconder on the raid, you just tell everyone &quot;The next Abscond across SG will be in 30 minutes.&quot;  You'll usually get a pile of pple there to move across SG all at one time.<br>
<br>
Best way still, tho, is to tell pple to learn how to camp through SG.<br>
